  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a staker, I want to be able to fail-over automatically to a secondary/tertiary Eth1 node so that if the primary Eth1 node is unavailable or incorrect I am able to continue to propose blocks correctly. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Configuration option to list a sequence of Eth1 nodes\r\n* Nodes are to be tried in the specified order\r\n* If the node I am connected to is unresponsive or incorrect, a different node should be selected. Order of retries is TBD (Start from the top again? Try round-robin?)\r\n* Helpful log warnings are emitted to alert the operator to what is happening",
